But if the same Cicero should defer to others in 11 1113 convictions, which he applied so resolutely and in such a grand manner when he bundled Antony out, he will find that he not only has thrown away his reputation for the future, but will also ensure that his past achievements shall be blotted out—for nothing is great in itself that does not bear the plain mark of reasoned judgement—; because no one man is better fitted to be a patriot and to champion liberty with wise thoughts or brave deeds, or with the devo- tion and the imperious call to leadership of the entire community. For these reasons we must not beg Octavius to deign to keep us safe. No, no! You must rouse yourself up, and realize that the state which was the scene of your greatest achievements will enjoy its freedom and honour on these terms alone, if leaders are forthcoming for the people in making a stand against the policies of reprobates.
